  description: "concurrent.futures._base.Executor length checks in cfexlen158 namespace — Executor.__module__.__len__()==24 ('concurrent.futures._base'=24: 'concurrent'=10+'.'=1+'futures'=7+'.'=1+'_base'=5=24; the module path length matches concurrent.futures.wait.__module__.__len__()==24 (established in extra157) because both are in the same _base submodule); Executor.__bases__[0].__name__.__len__()==6 ('object'=6: 'o'+'b'+'j'+'e'+'c'+'t'=6; Executor inherits from object, the root Python type); Executor.__name__.__len__()==8 ('Executor'=8); compare module lengths in the concurrent.futures family: '_base' submodule (len=24) vs top-level 'concurrent.futures' (len=18: 'concurrent'=10+'.'=1+'futures'=7=18); the _base submodule path is 6 chars longer because of '._base' (len=6 including dot); Executor.__dict__.__contains__('submit')==True (all four key methods are directly on Executor); verified with Python 3.14.3"
